# 🔍 File Searching Operations

## find
Used to search files and directories based on conditions.

### Search .txt files
```bash
find /home -name "*.txt"
Search only files
find . -type f
Search only directories
find . -type d
Search files larger than 1MB
find . -type f -size +1M
Search recently modified files
find . -mtime -1
🔎 Pattern Matching in Logs
grep

Used to search specific words or patterns inside files.

Search for ERROR logs
grep "ERROR" app.log
Case-insensitive search
grep -i "failed" app.log
Show line numbers
grep -n "warning" app.log
Count matching lines
grep -c "ERROR" app.log
🔁 Recursive Search Techniques
grep -r

Search text recursively inside directories.

Recursive search
grep -r "database" .
Recursive search with line numbers
grep -rn "server" .
📦 Large File Identification
Find files larger than 100MB
find / -type f -size +100M
Human-readable disk usage
du -sh *
Sort files by size
du -ah . | sort -rh | head -10
🔐 Secure Data Transfer
scp

Securely copy files between systems over SSH.

Copy file to remote server
scp file.txt user@server:/tmp/
Copy directory recursively
scp -r project/ user@server:/opt/
⏰ Restrict Cron Access
Allow a user
echo "devops" >> /etc/cron.allow
Deny a user
echo "testuser" >> /etc/cron.deny
🖥️ Default GUI Boot Configuration
Set GUI target
systemctl set-default graphical.target
Check current boot target
systemctl get-default
